<!--
VOICING PLAN (4107 — Christ The Lord Is Risen Today, G major):
- All F notes use accid.ges="s" (key sig F#).
- Shorter piece (8 bars) so texture builds quickly.
- Phase 1 (1-4): Light — quartal opening (G4-C5), 2-3 note RH, 3-note LH.
  - Bar 2: Am→D→G voice leading in all three staves moves in parallel fifths
    (avoided by RH keeping thirds).
  - Bar 3: first time RH reaches up to G5 (climax of phrase).
  - Bar 4: D7→G resolution with F#4 in both RH and LH.
- Phase 2 (5-8): Fuller — 4-note LH throughout, RH reaching G5 repeatedly.
  - Bar 5: RH C3→G5 on bar 3 (C chord), mirror of bar 3 climax.
  - Bar 6: "Eb" chord (non-diatonic) substituted with Bm — keeps smooth voice leading
    A→G→F# in inner voice.
  - Bar 7: RH F#5→G5 oscillation while LH descends G→C→B→E.
  - Bar 8: Final chord G2-D3-G3-D4 in LH gives deep, resonant close; RH fans G4→G5.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 2→3 RH: E5→G5→E5→G5 contrary to LH G→D→C→E motion.
- Bar 6: Eb substituted as Bm — A4-C5-E5 → G4-C5 → B4-D5-F#5 (stepwise thirds through).
- Bar 7: RH upper voice D5-F#5-D5-E5-G5 chromatic color with the F#.
- Bar 8: Low G2 in LH final chord provides pedal resonance.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 1-2: Light opening — quartal/open fifths RH, 2-3 note LH.
- Bars 3-4: Growing — 4-note LH chords, RH reaches G5 at phrase climax.
- Bars 5-6: Rich — full 4-note LH throughout, RH consistently 2-3 notes.
- Bars 7-8: Peak and close — bar 7 sustained high G5 in RH; bar 8 resolves
  down to low G2 in LH for deep final sonority.
-->
